ZK‑Device‑Trust‑mask

Device‑level trust attestation for the zk‑Mask Protocol.
Prove that a device is legitimate, untampered, and operating within acceptable risk boundaries — without exposing raw device secrets.

---

Overview

ZK‑Device‑Trust‑mask is the device integrity primitive in the zk‑Mask ecosystem. It collects hardware and environment signals (fingerprint, secure boot state, geolocation, patch level, etc.), computes a deterministic risk score, generates a zero‑knowledge proof of device posture, and records the attestation on‑chain. All verification flows are asynchronous and client‑side, preserving user privacy while enabling audit‑ready device access for federated intelligence, multi‑agent systems, and compliance‑sensitive operations.

This mask works hand‑in‑hand with:

· ZK‑Identity‑mask – binds a device to a pseudonymous identity
· ZK‑Browser‑mask – extends device trust to browser‑based sessions
· ZK‑Phone‑Activate‑mask – anchors the device attestation during mobile enrolment

