What’s Inside

Component Description
Risk Scoring Engine (src/risk_engine) Deterministic scoring module. Consumes device signals and outputs a bounded trust score. Pluggable rules, extensible for custom policies.
Off‑Chain Verification Daemon (daemon/) Async background service that performs device fingerprint verification, caches results, and acts as a ZK‑proof pre‑processor. Designed for RPC‑free, local‑first operation.
Multi‑Language SDKs Full‑stack client libraries: Rust (core logic + WASM), TypeScript (Node.js + browser), React Native (mobile), and plain ES modules. The most complete SDK across all masks.
Mobile Device Flow (sdk/typescript/src/mobile) Ready‑to‑use integration that collects phone hardware signals, generates proofs, and submits attestations — pairing directly with ZK‑Phone‑Activate‑mask.
On‑Chain Program (programs/) Solana program that stores device trust state, updates risk scores, and emits events consumable by GitHub App workflows and the compliance registry.
CI & Build Pipelines CodeQL for Rust & JS, Docker build/publish, staging & production deployment — everything needed for reproducible, audit‑ready releases.
Docs & Examples API references, batch operation guides, a full JS GitHub Action, and end‑to‑end test suites.

